# Frontend Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.production and fill in actual values for production
# DO NOT commit actual values - use Vercel's environment variables panel

# ==========================================
# REQUIRED FOR PRODUCTION
# ==========================================

# Convex Deployment URL (get from Convex dashboard)
REACT_APP_CONVEX_URL=https://your-convex-deployment.convex.cloud

# Backend API URL (optional - for legacy backend endpoints)
# Most API calls now go through Convex
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://your-backend-domain.vercel.app

# ==========================================
# CONVEX AUTH CONFIGURATION
# ==========================================
# These are configured in Convex dashboard, not here
# See convex/auth.config.ts for auth configuration
# Required Convex environment variables:
#   AUTH_AZURE_AD_CLIENT_ID - Your Azure AD app client ID
#   AUTH_AZURE_AD_CLIENT_SECRET - Your Azure AD app client secret
#   SITE_URL - Your application URL (for OAuth redirects)

# ==========================================
# AUTHENTICATION MODES
# ==========================================
# 1. SSO (Recommended): Sign in with Microsoft 365
#    - Configured via Convex Auth (convex/auth.config.ts)
#    - No frontend environment variables needed
#    - Users sign in with their work account
#
# 2. App-Only: Automated background tasks
#    - Configure credentials in the UI
#    - Requires client secret
#    - Used for service accounts
#
# 3. Demo Mode: Testing without credentials
#    - No configuration needed
#    - Mock authentication

# ==========================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST
# ==========================================
# [ ] Set REACT_APP_CONVEX_URL in Vercel Environment Variables
# [ ] Configure AUTH_AZURE_AD_* in Convex Dashboard
# [ ] Set SITE_URL in Convex Dashboard
# [ ] Do NOT commit .env file to git
# [ ] Use .env.example as template only